    dc:description "FIG. 5. — Nerineidae: A, Nerinea clymene d’Orbigny, 1850, figure from d’Orbigny 1851, Oxfordian, Châtel-Censoir (Yonne, France) MNHN.F.B12369; B, Nerinea mosae Deshayes, 1827, axial section, Oxfordian, Châtel-Censoir (Yonne, France), MNHN.F.R09444; C, Nerinea mosae, small specimen with almost complete aperture, Kimmeridgian, La Combe de Vaux (Ain,France),MNHN.F.A49004; D, Italoptygmatis digitalis Stoliczka in Stur, 1863, Cenomanian, Cherghes (Romania), NHMW 2013/0264/0001; E, F, Parasimploptyxis subturbinata (Pchelintsev, 1953), external view and axial section, Late Cretaceous, Goygol (Azerbaijan), NHMW 1847/XIII/22; G, Simploptyxis digitalis (Stoliczka, 1863), axial section, Cenomanian, Cherghes (Romania), NHMW 1853/III/30; H, Parasimploptyxis pailletteana (d’Orbigny, 1842), Turonian, Gams bei Hieflau (Austria), NHMW 2013/0051/0001; I, Simploptyxis ampla (Münster, 1844), axial section, Turonian,Gams bei Hieflau (Austria),NHMW 2002/0050/000; J, Plesioptygmatis sp., Late Middle Maastrichtian, Sabana" ;
